metadata.name: EPIHYPERDERPFLARDIOIDS #336
metadata.description:
EPIHYPERDERPFLARDIOIDS

after symbol 2525, 
aint gonna need to load, write no code
everything you think, do and say
is in the streams that you watch today (oh oh oh)

We find this code is very much alive. They are epi. They are hyper. They are derp. They are flardioids.

Epihyperderpflardioids is the name I have given to a large family of symmetrical loopy shapes, based on sine waves and rotations, reminiscent of the mathematical toy game "Spirograph", but also different. I studied them extensively, but don't claim to understand them fully, yet. I hope you enjoy them as much as I do.

These 365 Epihyperderpflardioids were generated for FXhash's one year anniversary.

metadata.name: Circumscript #99
metadata.description:
It has always been a goal of mine to incorporate the worlds of physical and digital art together in a piece. And with circumscript I am the closest I've ever been. Circumscript uses a custom shader written to mix and "dilute" the colors on the canvas, thus creating a very physical feeling piece.

This dilution can be more or less depending on the edition, but always plays a huge role in the feel of the piece.


Happy new year.


----


[m] or [double tap] : opens the export/settings menu, use this menu to change the resolution, and make sure to press the reload button if you do.
[holding down] : zooms in on a certain area of the piece, depending on where your mouse/finger is. Use this feature to expore the complex textures of the piece in more detail, it's highly recommended to do this on a higher resolution setting.

The outputs can vary slighty per device, as there's a slight difference in how certain math gets interpreted on different devices with shaders.


----


Made with p5.js and webgl by Wouter Missler in 2022/3.

metadata.name: Plottable Ricochets #14
metadata.description:
Plottable Ricochets explores polygon shapes scaled and rotated inside a parametric curve. The curve you obtain can widely vary.

More info: https://greweb.me/plots/361

The digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art: Owning this NFT confers the right to request a physical plot (A4 square, 21cm by 21cm) ‚Äì this is an optional possibility as you can already enjoy the digital version.

Digital and Physical art, hybrid and decoupled:
- art published via a digital NFT on Tezos ‚Äì its digital representation simulates fountain pen inks drawing on paper with animated effects.
- Token to the physical world: owning each NFT confer the power to request the related physical plot at https://greweb.me/plots/nft

Advanced plotting usecase: press "V" multiple times to increase lines collection when ink is too much for the paper.

@greweb ‚Äì 2021 ‚Äì tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM ‚Äì CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Origami. #8
metadata.description:
This piece, as suggested by the name, stems from an old art form that came from Japan about 1000 years ago. And has been practiced by people all around the world ever since.

My goal with this piece was to capture the feeling of origami and everything that comes with it, the paper texture, the delicate and often complicated folds, the colors, everything.

- Press [I] for information about your token (rarities, descriptions, etc.)
- Press [E] to open up the export settings, here you can export your token in up to 5000x5000 resolution.
- Press [<-] to show step counters, showing the process of the folds.

--------------------------------------------------

As for features, we have a couple:

Grid size: ranging from 1x1 all the way to 3x4
Color scheme: a total of 7 (possibly 9) color schemes are available.
Background: either dark or light.
Background feature: if your grid is 1x1 you can have background features.
Outlines: if you have outlines, your Origami will be transformed into Kirigami. (this is toggle-able)

metadata.name: Sedimentary Dissolution #150
metadata.description:
This piece is inspired by the geological processes related to sedimentary dissolution. Dissolution is a form of weathering which contributes to the creation of new rocks. In this piece, various algorithms take on the role of dissolution, producing visual recombinations of the original "sedimentary rock".

Instructions ::

p : save a hi-res image
e : toggle erosion on and off
s : toggle structure on and off
a : toggle all effects on and off

If offset, rgb dissolution or cross-bedding is true you can toggle it on and off.
If these features are false pressing the key will have no effect.

o : toggle offset on and off
r : toggle rgb dissolution on and off
c : toggle cross-bedding on and off

There are 20 versions you can explore, all using the same features.
Use the left and right arrow to change the random seed. 
Pressing space will re-instantiate the original random seed.

metadata.name: √âtudes(Reissued) #82
metadata.description:
√âtudes(Reissued) is a patched and upgraded version of √âtudes(Project #10993).

√âtudes was originally published on April 16, 2022. Because of technical issues (audio doesn‚Äôt play due to external link usage) we prepared this reissue to its current holders.

You can visit the original project with this link - https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/10993 


This reissue comprises of some fixes and additional new features as mentioned below;

New Features;

- New ‚Äòcolored‚Äô mode; now has colored noteheads and stems. Added new sampler for the colored mode: Marimba.
- Added a new synth for ‚Äòinverted & colored‚Äô mode; DuoSynth.

Fixes;

- Fixed canvas size to prevent additional notes being added in live mode. Now it‚Äôs consistent.
- Samples are now in the zip rather than in an external link, and won't break in the future.
- More consistent (but still sometimes buggy) sonification and audio playback.
- Fixed some minor issues and re-adjusted some probabilities.


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Click to start the sound -

‚Äò√âtudes‚Äô is a series of generative notation accompanied with sound.

‚Äò√âtudes‚Äô is the first series of the ‚ÄòNotations‚Äô collection. ‚ÄòNotations‚Äô will explore various notation techniques around the world and will use different sonification techniques and generative music algorithms.

In this series, a sonification process has been used to generate sound.

Some articulations or accidentals intentionally exist due to aesthetic preferences. For example there are some musically meaningless things like vibrato on a piano or a coda sign on a motif. And some notes will play the same pitch (even if they appear apart from one another) depending on the chosen scale.

Sonification tends to work better after 2nd (or even 3rd) play. Some minor audio bugs might occur.

There is a major but a rare bug which we intentionally kept in; it plays a generative piece from indicated pitches rather than just playing the motif only once.

There is a rare possibility that ‚Äò√âtudes‚Äô can generate an ‚Äòelectronic‚Äô result which plays with a FM synth instead of piano. 

Probabilities;

- 12 root notes

- 12 different scales

- Dynamics; pp,p,mp,mf,f,ff or none

- Dynamic changes; crescendo and diminuendo or none

- 4 different noteheads

- Several accidentals and articulations

- Vibrato might occur on some outputs

- 3 font styles

- 4 background textures


Made with p5.js
Ilgƒ±n ƒ∞√ß√∂z√º, March 2022(Reissued-September 2022)
@distcollective

metadata.name: RE/Posizioni #173
metadata.description:
Exactly one year ago I was minting my first fxhash project. 
‚ÄúPosizioni‚Äù was a quick sketch of only 25 editions that I put together to test this new platform and to my great surprise, it was the start of an amazing journey in this space that still continues to amaze me every day. 

‚ÄúRE/Posizioni‚Äù is an ideal continuation of my personal path that started one year ago: I decided to create an animated, glitchy, or even broken piece, something completely different from what I usually do as an artist and as a coder (and probably something I‚Äôm not very good at, forgive me for this :D ).
Even if this NFT crazy world is often uncertain, insecure, or unstable, we need to find a balance no matter how difficult, just as the lines in this artwork try to do.

Going out of my comfort zone, experimenting, or just having fun is what keeps this creative practice enjoyable for me, and it‚Äôs all that matters.

----

- Mouse click to pause the animation
- "s" key to download a png
- "f" key to full screen

Tested on Desktop/Chrome.
See LICENSE.md for more licensing details.

metadata.name: Isola della Scala #37
metadata.description:
All things pass, all things flow,
Movement, connection, separation, all in tow.
A misstep and we're knocked off course,
But in the end, we rise, as if by force.
Like a dance of dominoes, we fall and we stand,
In this ever-changing world, we're a part of the grand.

The name of this work is the name of the city where my roots began, where the path of everything changed and new directions in life were taken.

Made with p5.js, p5.grain and much love
